description.plain:
Strapping Young Lad were an extreme metal band from Vancouver, Canada and were active from 1994 until 2007.

The brainchild of singer, multi instrumentalist and songwriter Devin Townsend, Strapping Young Lad paired the sonic aggression of bands like Fear Factory and Napalm Death with extensive multitracking to create a “Wall of Sound” production style that was unlike anything of the era.

Despite increasing critical success and an ever growing fanbase, Townsend (who would be diagnosed with bipolar disorder in 1998) would end the band in 2007 due to his belief that the mental extremes the band required him to go to were too detrimental on his health.

Band


Devin Townsend – Vocals, Guitars, Keyboards (1994-2007)
Jed Simon – Guitars, Backing vocals (1995-2007)
Byron Stroud – Bass, Backing vocals (1996-2007)
Gene Hoglan – Drums (1996-2007)

body.plain: ‘Love?’ is the sole single promoting Alien and one of the  band’s most comercially successful songs. A music video inspired by a cult horror movie ‘The Evil Dead’ was made for this song and aired on Headbanger’s Ball. The song was written way before the rest of the album and it was initially going to appear on never released EP in 2003.

body.plain:
Strapping Young Lad were an extreme metal band from Vancouver, Canada and were active from 1994 until 2007.

The brainchild of singer, multi instrumentalist and songwriter Devin Townsend, Strapping Young Lad paired the sonic aggression of bands like Fear Factory and Napalm Death with extensive multitracking to create a “Wall of Sound” production style that was unlike anything of the era.

Despite increasing critical success and an ever growing fanbase, Townsend (who would be diagnosed with bipolar disorder in 1998) would end the band in 2007 due to his belief that the mental extremes the band required him to go to were too detrimental on his health.

Band


Devin Townsend – Vocals, Guitars, Keyboards (1994-2007)
Jed Simon – Guitars, Backing vocals (1995-2007)
Byron Stroud – Bass, Backing vocals (1996-2007)
Gene Hoglan – Drums (1996-2007)
